What are the similarities between the simulation of the farmer, the teacher, and the gobstones?
All of them have the same logical structure: distributing some elements and then recollecting
some other elements resulting from those.
Basically, the three alternatives are different ways of visualize the execution of a single program.

> **Attires**
>
> Attires are a way to change the way in which program effects are visualized on the board.
> Using them, we can represent any element using only stones.
